      "message": "[Major] Line 1972: 🟡 Suggestions: `loadMissingBodyOverwrites()` only signals messages when the plugin returns a non-empty overwrite. If a message already had a stale overwrite before a reload and the plugin now returns no overwrite, the stale data remains unless `reloadBodyOverwriteMessages()` was used. This makes the API behavior depend on which refresh entry point was called. Consider erasing missing/empty overwrite results for processed messages and signalling affected parents when the value changes.",
