      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2048: 🔴 Critical Issues: `updateMessageBodyOverwrite()` writes an edition commit\u0027s overwrite onto the parent message. If `messageId` is an older edition, this corrupts the parent/current body overwrite and can make clients display the wrong text for the current message body. Store the overwrite only on the commit it belongs to, then emit the parent with edition overwrites injected.\n```suggestion\nif (const auto editIt \u003d it-\u003esecond-\u003ebody.find(CommitKey::EDIT);\n    editIt !\u003d it-\u003esecond-\u003ebody.end() \u0026\u0026 !editIt-\u003esecond.empty()) {\n    const auto parentIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(editIt-\u003esecond);\n    if (parentIt \u003d\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()) {\n        return;\n    }\n    signalMsg \u003d injectEditionOverwrites(*parentIt-\u003esecond, loadedHistory_.quickAccess);\n} else {\n    signalMsg \u003d injectEditionOverwrites(*it-\u003esecond, loadedHistory_.quickAccess);\n}\n```",
      "revId": "055abc280f1f60d21f55d5b30420814ce746552b",
